FBIS3-17072 "drsov056_b_94019" FBIS-SOV-94-056 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Grachev on Strengthening Air Defense Forces LD2203203294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 22 Mar 94 LD2203203294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Army General Pavel Grachev, Russia's defense minister, has denied reports of a 50 percent reduction in the country's air defense forces. The minister said that the present air defense structure would not only be maintained but additionally strengthened with fighter aircraft. In the development of the air defense forces, priority will be given to modern aircraft and missiles and radio-technical means of reconnaissance.
